I would fix Place.java in four steps.
1. Remove the composite key. The SQL table has PRIMARY KEY (place_page_id), not (place_page_id, parent_page_id), so PlaceId.java should not be the entity ID.
2. Make Place a page-backed subtype. Place.place_page_id is a foreign key to Page.page_id, so Place should model “a specialized page”, not a standalone table with an embedded key. I would make Place extend Page.java and use @PrimaryKeyJoinColumn(name = "place_page_id").
3. Treat parent_page_id as a normal field or self-reference. It should be a regular column like parentPageId or a self-reference like private Place parentPlace, not part of the primary key.
4. Align validation with the schema. Right now the entity requires name, hours, and priceRange, but the SQL columns are nullable in KooweV1_0_9.sql (line 428). We should either:
